# Sentra Cursor Index

## Authority

1. Patient safety, PHI/PII protection, and secrets handling.
2. Root `AGENTS.md`.
3. Root `.agent/` operational state.
4. Nearest local `AGENTS.md`.
5. `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.

Cursor rules are supplementary. They do not override `AGENTS.md`.

## Rule Set

| File                            | Purpose                                                                                     |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `.cursor/rules/00-core.mdc`     | Identity, context guard, task class, GO gate, communication, session logging, verification. |
| `.cursor/rules/10-backend.mdc`  | API, database, Prisma, NestJS, CQRS, FHIR, PHI/PII backend guardrails.                      |
| `.cursor/rules/20-frontend.mdc` | React, Next.js, UI components, accessibility, design tokens.                                |
| `.cursor/rules/30-quality.mdc`  | TypeScript, tests, monorepo conventions, verification, review, gold-standard references.    |
| `.cursor/permissions.json`      | Team allowlist + block rules (Run Mode UI lock in Settings).                                |
| `.cursor/skills/`               | Repo workflow skills — verify, handoff, app-boundary preflight.                             |

## Operating Rule

Use the smallest applicable rule set. Attach target app/package paths with `@path` when context is thin.

Workflow + permissions: [`docs/guides/008-cursor-permissions-and-workflows.md`](../docs/guides/008-cursor-permissions-and-workflows.md).
